title: ‘Direct selling industry grows 12%’
description: The Indian Direct Selling Association's annual survey revealed a 12% growth in India's direct selling industry, surpassing Rs 21,000 crore in turnover for 2022-23. Wellness and nutraceutical products led the way, making up 73.5% of sales, while cosmetics & personal care accounted for 11.3%. Over four years, the industry saw an 8.3% CAGR.

title: ‘Jobs-linked PLI scheme to boost several sectors’
US Federal Reserve holds rates again over ‘elevated’ inflation
description: The US Federal Reserve opted to keep interest rates unchanged on Wednesday. However, policymakers signaled a plan to gradually decrease rates by three-quarters of a percentage point by the end of 2024. The central bank acknowledged slower progress towards achieving its 2% inflation goal. In its latest update, the Fed highlighted that inflation continues to be high.

title: SC: ED's multiple chargesheets lead to delay in trial
description: Supreme Court criticizes delays by Enforcement Directorate, emphasizes immediate trial initiation after chargesheet filing to prevent prolonged custody without trial. Justice system urged to ensure speedy trials for accused individuals.

title: HDFC sells company that spawned education loan business
description: HDFC Bank announced the sale of its education loan subsidiary, HDFC Credila, for Rs 9,552 crore to a group of investors led by Baring Private Equity Asia and ChrysCapital. This move valued the company at Rs 10,350 crore. The sale was triggered by a regulation prohibiting the bank from owning its acquired education loan entity post its merger with parent company HDFC last year.

title: NEET-UG applications surge for 9th year in a row, record 24L
description: NEET-UG achieves record registrations with 24 lakh applicants for 2024-25. Competition eases slightly with 6,000 new seats in govt colleges. Female participation peaks at 57.2%.

title: SP Group sells data centre construction business for Rs 700 crore
description: The Shapoorji Pallonji Group is stepping away from its data centre construction business in India. The business has been sold for Rs 700 crore to a consortium of 30 investors, a unique move in the M&A landscape. Among the investors are Ashish Kacholia, Mukul Mahavir Agrawal, Yash Kela, and Nikhil Vora, showcasing a diverse ownership structure for the venture.

title: Zelenskyy invites PM to Kyiv, hopes India to attend Global Peace Summit
description: PM Modi spoke with Putin and Zelenskyy and reiterated its position for the resolution of the Russia-Ukraine conflict through dialogue and diplomacy. Zelenskyy expressed gratitude for India's support and invited PM Modi to Ukraine. He also hoped India to participate in the Global Peace Summit. They discussed the brics summit and Special & Privileged Strategic Partnerships.

title: Abhishek gets SC relief from ED summonses during polls
description: Supreme Court grants Abhishek Banerjee and Rujira relief from ED summons during Lok Sabha polls, adjourning the hearing. Abhishek contests 2024 polls from Diamond Harbour, showing cooperation with investigating agencies.

title: ED out to arrest me, won’t appear before it, Kejriwal tells HC
description: AAP chief and Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal resists ED appearance, doubts arrest near elections. HC probes money laundering. Singhvi, an advocate presenting Kejriwal, defends, AAP challenging the law. ASG accuses privilege. Kejriwal was summoned for the 9 times. Following a recommendation by LG V K Saxena, the CBI registered an FIR, which subsequently resulted in the money laundering probe.

title: India will take lead in AI, says PM Modi
description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi highlighted the potential of Artificial Intelligence (AI) for the country's youth, stating that India is poised to excel in this field. Without naming Congress MP Rahul Gandhi, Modi emphasized the importance of experimentation and quick adaptation in both startups and politics. Modi's remarks underscored the need for a proactive approach in embracing new technologies to stay ahead in the global arena.

title: CCI denies interim relief to local companies in Google case
description: The Competition Commission of India (CCI) rejected the interim relief pleas from local app developers seeking to halt Google from enforcing fees or commissions under its updated payments policy. People Interactive India, Mebigo Labs, Indian Broadcasting and Digital Foundation (IBDF), and Indian Digital Media Industry Foundation (IDMIF) had filed the pleas.

title: Sadhguru recovering after brain surgery
description: Sadhguru underwent brain surgery for excessive bleeding, now in recovery. No specific timeline for resuming daily routine post-surgery, following severe headaches and hospitalization due to chronic and fresh bleeding.

title: JSW MG Motor India plans to recreate ‘Maruti movement’
description: Indian and Chinese companies have teamed up for a significant joint venture in the automotive sector. SAIC, a leading Chinese automaker that owns MG Motor, has partnered with Indian steel giant JSW to produce cars for both domestic and global markets. The new entity, JSW MG Motor India, will have 51% ownership by Indian firms. Initial investment for the venture is set at Rs 5,000 crore, as confirmed by Sajjan Jindal, chairman of JSW group.

title: Robbed solar panels now powering Maoists
description: Maoists in Bastar rely on stolen and ordered solar panels to power gadgets, adapting to security force pressure by frequently changing camps. The insurgency benefits from the robbery, highlighting a concerning trend amidst the Centre's electrification project for tribal groups.

title: Army inducts first lot of desi anti-drone systems for China border deployment
description: The Indian Army has introduced seven new indigenous integrated drone detection and interdiction systems (IDD&IS) along the northern borders with China. These systems can jam hostile drones and use lasers to eliminate them, with a detection range of 5 to 8 km. Additionally, DRDO is developing more potent directed energy weapon systems like high-energy lasers and high-powered microwaves for enhanced security measures.

title: Gujarat to punish victims, witnesses if ragging incidents not reported
description: In a move to tackle ragging, the Gujarat government will now crack down on educational institutions that fail to report incidents. Perpetrators, as well as witnesses and victims of ragging, must be flagged to the authorities. The government resolution (GR) was issued on Tuesday and brought to the attention of the Gujarat high court on Wednesday following a ragging incident at BJ Medical College in Ahmedabad last year.

title: Centre notifies PIB’s fact check unit
description: The Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology has officially established the Centre's 'fact check unit' in accordance with IT rules, as announced by the Press Information Bureau. This development follows a recent decision by the Bombay High Court to not prevent the Centre from setting up the FCU, a matter now under scrutiny by the Supreme Court.

title: Bengaluru neighbours fight over ‘open window sex’
description: Bengaluru homemaker files police complaint against neighbors for visible bedroom activities through a window, sparking a legal conflict. Landlord's wife counters, escalating the situation. Both parties face legal consequences under the Indian Penal Code.

title: Discordant note: Carnatic singers protest against award for musician
description: Renowned Carnatic artists Ranjani and Gayathri, along with Harikatha exponent Dushyanth Sridhar, have decided to boycott the Music Academy's upcoming festival in Chennai. This move comes in response to the recent awarding of Sangita Kalanidhi to T M Krishna by the academy. Ranjani and Gayathri have opted out of their scheduled performance on Dec 25 and will not take part in the conference from Dec 15 to Jan 1.

title: Congress finalises names for 12 Lok Sabha seats in Maharashtra
description: Congress has selected candidates for 12 Lok Sabha seats in Maharashtra, with Praniti Shinde set to run from Solapur, her father Sushil Kumar Shinde's previous constituency. Sahu Maharaj is the likely contender for Kolhapur. The party is urging Vijay Waddetiwar, leader of the opposition, to stand for Chandrapur, though he prefers his daughter, Shivani, a young leader, to contest from there instead.

title: Budaun man kills neighbour's sons, shot dead in ‘encounter’
description: Mohd Sajid allegedly slit Vinod Thakur's sons' throats over a monetary dispute, sparking communal tension. Javed, his accomplice, is on the run. According to the police, Sajid attacked the siblings when parents were not at home. While he cut the throats of the other two brothers, the third one survived with minor injuries. Sajid died in a police encounter.

title: Bahubali barred from polls finds suitable ‘candidate’
description: Convicted lawbreaker Ashok Mahto of Nawada district recently announced on social media his search for an "ideal bride." The 60-year-old tied the knot with 46-year-old Kumari Anita, a Delhi resident, on Tuesday. Mahto eyes an RJD ticket for a family member from Munger to challenge JD(U) heavyweight Lalan Singh. If Anita contests, she faces a tough political debut.

title: Centre to SC: For 73 years, ECs appointed exclusively by government
description: Responding to objections against the selection of election commissioners (ECs) by a panel consisting of the Prime Minister, a Cabinet minister, and the leader of the opposition, the government informed the Supreme Court that historically, ECs have been appointed solely by the government without any specific legislation. The government highlighted that the Supreme Court had only established a temporary process for EC selection due to a legislative gap.

title: Delhi HC highlights ‘voter wisdom’, junks plea to punish oppn trio
description: Delhi HC refused to consider a plea to prosecute Rahul Gandhi, Arvind Kejriwal, and Akhilesh Yadav for allegedly making false statements to harm the nation's image. The court emphasized that Indian voters' judgment should not be underestimated, as they can discern between leaders and misleading information. HC declined to intervene, saying the wisdom of the Indian voters should not be underestimated.

title: ‘Those trying to bleed us are now suffering’: PM Modi
description: PM Modi emphasized India's global growth recognition, impact on terror leaders, and technology use against corruption, leading to panic among politicians with hidden cash bundles. Addressing the Conclave, PM Modi said the next five years would be crucial to continue the country’s growth journey even as he recalled how the past 10 years had witnessed overall growth.

title: Miffed Mahayuti netas make a beeline to meet Sharad for ticket
description: Disgruntled Mahayuti alliance leaders, who missed out on nominations, are turning to veteran Sharad Pawar for Lok Sabha chances in MVA. Beed's NCP figure Bajrang Sonawane, once with Ajit Pawar, joined NCP(SCP) in Pune. Pankaja Munde's BJP candidacy in Beed led Sonawane to switch sides, eyeing a new path. Pawar mentioned candidate discussions before Beed's final decision.

title: ‘BJP may give Raj Thackeray seats for only state, civic polls’
description: MNS leader Raj Thackeray to convene a core committee meeting on Thursday, according to Clara Lewis. Sources reveal Thackeray, engaged with BJP, may not get a Lok Sabha seat but could be considered for assembly and local body polls. In exchange, he will support Mahayuti in the upcoming Lok Sabha elections, as per sources.

title: SP buries buzz over Varun Gandhi, unveils pick from Pilibhit
description: Pilibhit BJP MP Varun Gandhi will not be joining forces with Akhilesh Yadav's Samajwadi Party, as confirmed by SP's latest candidate list. Bhagwat Saran Gangwar has been nominated by SP for the Pilibhit seat, replacing the incumbent. Gangwar, a veteran five-time MLA from Nawabganj in Bareilly, had previously contested the 2019 Lok Sabha elections from Bareilly under the SP banner.

title: Raft of inductions for Congress: An MP, an MLA, and a party
description: Suspended BSP MP from Amroha, Danish Ali, has officially joined the Congress, citing his determination to combat divisive elements in the nation. Former Bihar MP Pappu Yadav also united his Janadhikar Party with the Congress, and Jharkhand assembly's BJP whip Jai Prakash Patel followed suit, marking a series of new inductions that the opposition party views as a positive sign leading up to the upcoming Lok Sabha elections.

title: Death at mall: Baby slips off father’s hands, falls 3 floors
description: A year-old infant fell 40 feet at a Raipur mall after slipping from her father's arms on the third floor. The tragic incident was captured on CCTV, leading to a quick response from bystanders who rushed the baby to the hospital.

title: Cong chances not bright, says Pratibha Singh, to skip LS polls
description: In a setback to the struggling Congress in Himachal Pradesh, Mandi MP Pratibha Singh declared on Wednesday that she would not run in the Lok Sabha elections, stating that "elections can't be contested by merely distributing MPLADS funds." Pratibha, after participating in the Congress screening committee meeting in New Delhi on Tuesday to deliberate on the Himachal seats, expressed skepticism about the party's prospects in the current scenario.

title: Age bar flouted? Centre seeks Moose Wala parents’ IVF details
description: Union health ministry investigates Sidhu Moose Wala's mother's IVF process as she conceived the child at the age of 58 in Bathinda, which is against the ART act. According to the law, the ART Act, 2021 age limit is 21-50. Penalties for violations include fines and imprisonment. Punjab's principal secretary is involved.

title: Educational institutions from Telangana bought bonds worth crores
description: Telangana educational institutions, including Sri Chaitanya Students Facility Management and Varsity Education Management, were found to have purchased electoral bonds worth crores, according to ECI records. T Sharks Overseas Education Consultancy is also on the list. Sri Chaitanya purchased bonds worth Rs 10 crore on April 8, 2022, and Rs 6 crore on Jan 11, 2024.

title: IS India chief arrested in Assam after infiltration from Bangladesh
description: Assam Police arrested IS India chief Haris Farooqi and an accomplice in Dhubri district for planning sabotage activities. Farooqi, a key figure in the Delhi IS terror module, faces pending cases and will be handed over to NIA. Based on inputs from sister agencies, Assam Police rushed its STF team to Dhubri on Tuesday to locate and apprehend the two.

title: Amit Shah says 90% of BJP funds came when poll code was in place
description: Amid anticipation for the Election Commission's impending disclosure of electoral bond details, Home Minister Amit Shah dismissed allegations of BJP pressuring corporate houses via ED and income tax for poll funds through EBs. Shah revealed that 90% of the party's contributions came post the declaration of poll dates. The home minister said the pre-EB regime suited opposition parties.

title: INDIA govt will junk CAA, UCC, rein in governors: DMK in manifesto
description: M K Stalin's DMK unveiled its Lok Sabha manifesto, focusing on key commitments in line with the INDIA bloc's objectives. These include undoing the BJP-led central government's decisions on CAA and UCC, restoring J&K's statehood, and repealing Article 356. In Tamil Nadu, DMK's pledge to limit Raj Bhavan's powers gains significance amid ongoing tensions between the Stalin administration and Governor R N Ravi.

title: 'Take action against Union min for linking Tamils to B'luru blast'
description: Election Commission directs Karnataka CEO to take action on DMK complaint against Shobha Karandlaje's statement linking Tamil Nadu people to Bengaluru bomb blast. Compliance report requested within 48 hours. Terming Karandlaje’s remarks as a violation of Section 123(3) and Section 125 and as well as the model code of conduct, Tamil Nadu’s ruling party sought action against the minister and BJP.

title: 2 Pak students get death penalty for killing teacher over 'blasphemy'
description: Three female seminary students, Razia Hanfi, Ayesha Naumani, and Umra Aman, have been sentenced for the murder of their teacher, Safoora Bibi, on blasphemy charges in northwestern Pakistan. The incident occurred at Jamia Islamia Falahul Binaat seminary in Dera Ismail Khan district. Two students received the death penalty, while one was given life imprisonment.

title: Militants storm Gwadar port complex, 7 killed
description: Baloch separatists attacked Pakistan's Gwadar Port Authority Complex, linked to the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor. Seven assailants were killed in the attack. The assault targeted government offices and intelligence agencies. The attack is seen as a response to China's investment in the region. The Majeed Brigade, a suicide squad of the proscribed Balochistan Liberation Army (BLA), claimed responsibility for the attack.

title: IMF, Pak reach staff-level agreement for $1.1 billion loan
description: Pakistan and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) have clinched a deal for the release of $1.1 billion as part of a $3 billion bailout package. This financial aid aims to prevent Pakistan from defaulting on its debts. The agreement, marking the final review of Pakistan's stabilisation programme, was confirmed by Nathan Porter, the IMF team leader.

title: Khalistan supporter jailed for stabbing 3 with kirpan in UK
description: A Khalistan supporter, Gurpreet Singh, 26, has been sentenced to 28 months in jail for stabbing two Indian-origin men and a female police officer with a kirpan during last year's Indian Independence Day celebrations in Southall. Singh, an Indian citizen, was found carrying three kirpans, using one with a 20cm blade in the attack. He was also ordered to surrender all three kirpans to the court.

title: J&K woman, who entered PoK with infant daughter, repatriated
description: A 22-year-old woman and her daughter were repatriated from PoK to Poonch after crossing the LoC. There is still no clarity on where they have stayed for one month but the sources said that they might have stayed with relatives. Her husband filed a missing FIR and said that his wife and daughter left the house after the argument and didn't return.

title: US tests hypersonic missile from pacific base of Gaum
description: The US tested hypersonic weapon in the Pacific amid competition with China and Russia. Earlier, North Korea also tested a solid-fuel engine for a hypersonic missile targeting the US Pacific territory of Guam, where American military bases are located, and possibly Alaska.  Three U.S. military bases are located on the island.

title: Watch: Maxwell hilariously imitates Kohli’s batting style
description: IPL 2024 begins with Chennai Super Kings facing Royal Challengers Bengaluru on March 22. Virat Kohli trains at MA Chidambaram Stadium, with Glenn Maxwell mimicking him in a viral video. RCB rebranded at RCB Unbox event.

title: Priyanka Chopra drops photos with Ram Lalla
description: Netizens gush over Priyanka Chopra as she drops glimpses of her Ram Mandir visit. Fans say her daughter Malti Marie is looking like little Sita in a bindi. The actress wrote, "Blessings for the little one and family" as she shared these moments on social media!

title: Devoleena Bhattacharjee reacts to Shark Deepinder Goyal's pure veg fleet
description: Devoleena reacts to Deepinder's pure veg fleet, respecting choices. Deepinder updates fleet, ensuring safety for all partners. Red uniforms to avoid food associations. Twitter updates address non-vegetarians. Safety measures for delivery partners against societal issues.

title: Rohit, Hardik hug each other, chat at MI camp
description: Seemingly, harmony reigns in the Mumbai Indians camp. On Wednesday evening at the Wankhede Stadium, MI captain Hardik Pandya and the franchise's former skipper and Indian captain Rohit Sharma embraced each other warmly and engaged in a pleasant conversation before the team's final intra-squad practice match, ahead of IPL 2024.

title: PM Modi's two-day visit to Bhutan postponed: MEA
'Kuch bol deta hun, jo mic pe pakda jata hai': Rohit
description: During the recently-concluded India-England Test series, Rohit Sharma's stump mic chatter garnered significant attention, with his witty one-liners quickly going viral on social media. Having previously clarified that he doesn't engage in it intentionally, the Indian skipper revisited the issue, explaining that his comments are occasionally captured by the stump mic.

title: Isis India head, aide arrested from Assam's Dhubri
description: The ISIS (Islamic State of Iraq and Syria) is designated as a terrorist organization by numerous countries and international organizations, including the United Nations, due to its extremist ideologies and involvement in acts of terrorism globally.

title: Shifting tides in American perceptions: 'China number 1 enemy'
Sadhguru undergoes emergency brain surgery at Apollo in Delhi
description: Spiritual guru and founder of the Isha Foundation, Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev, has undergone emergency brain surgery at Apollo Hospital in Delhi after massive swelling and bleeding in his brain. According to the Isha Foundation, Sadguru was examined by Dr Vinit Suri, a senior consultant neurologist at Apollo Hospitals and was advised to undergo an MRI, where massive bleeding in his brain was detected.

title: EC to look into DMK's complaint against Karandlaje
description: The Election Commission of India (ECI) has directed the Chief Electoral Officer (CEO) of Karnataka to investigate a complaint filed by the DMK against BJP leader and Union Minister of State, Shobha Karandlaje, for allegedly breaching the Model Code of Conduct (MCC). Karandlaje had made controversial remarks linking people from Tamil Nadu to criminal activities during a protest in Bengaluru.

title: With more women, K'taka voter ratio at nearly 1:1
description: As per the figures released on March 16, there are 999 females per 1,000 in Karnataka, better than the 997 in the final draft released in Jan 2024. However, young voters buck this trend, just as in Jan to touch 858 from 856 two months ago. Skewed ratio among young voters could be for multiple reasons, but as TOI had reported in Jan, it is primarily attributed to poor sex ratio at birth during 2005-06.

title: PM Modi shares these six big numbers for startups in India
description: PM Modi emphasized India's AI potential, urged global solutions at Startup Mahakumbh. Shared startup stats and plans for AI development. Encouraged research funding and innovation in sunrise sectors.

title: Best phones under 25000: Top Choices from brands
description: Though the market for mobile phones under Rs. 25,000 has always been lucrative, the year 2024 has been particularly exciting with the launch of several state-of-the-art options. After thoroughly researching and considering thousands of online reviews and ratings, we have enlisted in this article some of the most technologically advanced handsets that you can buy within Rs. 25,000 and from top brands.

title: 'Rohit sacked here as well': Netizens react on MI's team bonding video
description: Social media has been abuzz with speculations ever since Hardik Pandya took over as the Mumbai Indians skipper from Rohit Sharma, suggesting that there might be unrest within the MI camp.

title: Another British Royal family photo creates 'controversy', here's why
description: Getty Images dispute digitally manipulated photos released by Kensington Palace, including images of Queen Elizabeth II and young royals. The controversy questions the authenticity of edited royal family photos and raises concerns about misinformation.

title: Langer terms Dravid lucky, avoids question on coaching Team India
description: After taking a two-year hiatus following his widely-publicized and acrimonious exit from the head coach position of the Australian team in 2022, Justin Langer has returned as the head coach of IPL franchise Lucknow Super Giants.  Although he faced a straight question upfront, Langer chose not to provide a direct response, leaving the speculation surrounding his future coaching endeavors open-ended.

title: Centre notifies Fact Check Unit under PIB
PM Modi speaks to Zelenskyy, supports peace efforts in Ukraine
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi conversed with Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, emphasizing bolstering the India-Ukraine partnership and extending support for peace efforts in the ongoing conflict. Modi assured continued humanitarian aid, following a dialogue with Russian President Vladimir Putin, advocating for dialogue and diplomacy to resolve the Russia-Ukraine conflict, amidst questions over Putin's reelection victory.

title: Shakti row: BJP complains to EC over Rahul's 'obnoxious' remarks
Unidentified gunmen open fire at Pakistan's Gwadar port, 2 killed
'Paras has to decide if ...': Chirag on uncle walking out of NDA
Zomato's 'green uniform row': Swiggy makes important clarification
description: Swiggy has released a statement to clarify that a controversial advertisement that has been circulating on social media is fake and not affiliated with the company. The ad, which appears to criticise Zomato's recent "Pure Veg Mode" and "Pure Veg Fleet" initiatives, was created by a user on X (formerly Twitter) and shared widely on various social media platforms.

title: India tests first indigenously made engine for battle tanks
'He actually knows my name': Patil goes crazy after meeting Kohli
description: RCB emerged victorious in the WPL final, led by Shreyanka Patil's exceptional performance. Patil emerged as the standout performer of the night, cementing her place as the leading wicket-taker in the WPL. With an impressive tally of 13 scalps, Patil played a pivotal role in securing victory for her team.

title: 'Indian-origin Varadkar to step down as Ireland's PM'
Shaun Romy on her journey to being diagnosed with alopecia
description: Actor-model Shaun Romy talks exclusively to ETimes for the first time, about her journey of healing after being diagnosed with the autoimmune condition, alopecia areata, that causes the hair to fall out in patches. “I had to stay positive. Since childhood, my hair has been my greatest source of confidence. Coming to terms with losing was a different ball game altogether. For a while, I wore wigs, but then I didn’t feel like it," she opens up.

title: 'Dhoni knew long back, cricket is important but...'
description: Former India fast bowler Zaheer Khan has expressed his views on Chennai Super Kings skipper Mahendra Singh Dhoni's interests beyond cricket, and said that the World Cup winning captain understood a long time ago that "cricket is important but it's not everything". Dhoni is all set to lead CSK in the 17th edition of the Indian Premier League, starting from March 22. The 42-year-old has been leading the side since the league's inaugural edition in 2008.

title: 'Shortcomings' during rule: Vietnam President Vo Van Thuong resigns
description: Vietnam President Vo Van Thuong resigned due to 'shortcomings' affecting public opinion and violating party rules. His resignation is linked to the anti-bribery campaign in Vietnam, impacting business sentiment and policy decisions.

title: What Fadnavis said on Raj Thackeray and Amit Shah's meet
'Virat is certainly...': Smith on Kohli's place in T20 WC squad
description: The cricketing world was rocked last week by a major shock as reports surfaced suggesting that Virat Kohli might face exclusion from India's T20 World Cup squad. "What we know is that he plays extremely well under pressure. He loves that. It's those players who you want in your team when you go into the World Cup and face pressure situations. You want the experienced players who stand up in those situations, and Virat is certainly one of those," Smith said.

title: 'Will not tolerate ...': Pak PM's warning to Kabul
Pappu Yadav merges Jan Adhikar Party with Congress
description: Pappu Yadav merged Jan Adhikar Party with Congress at AICC. Speculation arose after meeting RJD's Lalu Prasad Yadav in Madhepura. His wife, Ranjeet Ranjan, is a Rajya Sabha member. It comes a day after the Bihar leader called on RJD supremo Lalu Prasad Yadav fueling suspicion about a realignment with the party that fielded him from Madhepura in the 2014 Lok Sabha elections.

title: 'Even Dhoni made blunders but never seen Rohit doing it'
description: Former Indian wicket-keeper Parthiv Patel recently drew comparisons between the leadership styles of Rohit Sharma, ex-Mumbai Indians captain, and MS Dhoni, the iconic leader of the Chennai Super Kings in the Indian Premier League (IPL). According to Patel, Rohit's captaincy has been marked by a consistent avoidance of major errors or blunders, contrasting with instances where Dhoni, over the course of his illustrious IPL career, may have made occasional mistakes.

title: Builder’s error in allotting flat won't impact tax benefit claim: ITAT
UK privacy watchdog probes Kate Middleton’s medical data 'breach'
description: The UK's privacy watchdog is probing a hospital staff's attempt to access Kate Middleton's medical records during surgery at The London Clinic. The hospital launched an internal investigation after a staffer tried to view Princess Kate's notes. Information Commissioner's Office is assessing the breach report. The hospital notified Kensington Palace, emphasizing patient privacy and past breaches' tragic consequences.

title: IPL 2024: How to watch RCB vs CSK IPL match live in USA
description: IPL 17th edition commences with CSK vs RCB on March 22. Watch on Cricbuzz with ABOUND for free. Experience T20 action, playoffs, and the grand finale of IPL 2024. Don't miss the ultimate cricketing spectacle!

title: PM Modi speaks to Putin, discusses Ukraine
DMK manifesto: These promises make it INDIA bloc’s manifesto
description: The DMK manifesto virtually read like the manifesto of the INDIA bloc as many of the promises could be delivered only by the central government.

title: Priyanka Chopra and Nick Jonas visit Ram Mandir with daughter
description: Priyanka Chopra, Nick Jonas, and daughter visited Ram temple in Ayodhya. They attended pre-Holi party, supported 'Women of My Billion' movie. Nick spotted at Ritesh Sidhwani's party.

title: Centre defends appointment of 2 new ECs under new rules
description: The Centre has filed an affidavit in the Supreme Court defending the appointment of two election commissioners under the chief election commissioner and Other election commissioners Act, 2023. It argues that the Act safeguards the Election Commission's constitutional integrity and fosters democratic mechanisms. Excluding the Chief Justice of India from the selection panel is upheld, citing independence not reliant on judicial presence.

title: Assam to become major semiconductor player, says Ratan Tata
description: Ratan Tata lauded Tata Group's investment in Assam's semiconductor plant, enhancing cancer care and positioning Assam as a major semiconductor player. PM Modi's semiconductor focus and IT Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw's chip production commitment were highlighted. Tatas, in collaboration with the Assam government, has already set up several cancer care hospitals across the state.

title: Centre seeks response over Moosewala's mother's IVF
ED cannot keep filing chargesheets to keep accused in jail: SC
description: The Supreme Court criticised Enforcement Directorate for denying default bail through continuous chargesheets, resulting in extending investigations and thus indefinite jail time. Justices Sanjiv Khanna and Dipankar Datta expressed concern over prolonged detentions without trial, focusing on the case of Prem Prakash linked to illegal mining. According to CrPC, a person arrested for an offense is entitled to default bail if the investigating authorities fail to complete the investigation or submit a chargesheet within the specified timeline, typically 60 or 90 days.

title: Instagram is down for several users globally
description: Meta's Instagram globally down. Users report on X. 21% face app access issues, 69% login problems. Outage ongoing since yesterday. Specific X posts. Meta services normal despite outage.

title: Woman doctor jumps off Atal Setu sea bridge; note found
description: Woman doctor from Thane, Maharashtra feared dead after jumping into Arabian sea from Atal Setu, longest sea bridge connecting south Mumbai with Navi Mumbai. Incident on Monday, body not found yet. Taxi driver involved, suicide note citing depression.

title: 'He said to me…..': Nvidia CEO recalls his meeting with PM Modi
description: Jensen Huang commended Indian engineers for their AI skills in front office value creation. Their transition to the front room of companies is essential for India to lead the AI revolution, supported by initiatives like the India Artificial Intelligence Mission. “He (PM Modi) said to me, Jensen, India should not export flour to import bread, this makes perfect sense. Why export the raw material to import the value add. Why export the data of India, so that you can import AI,” Huang said.

title: Holi 2024: Will banks be closed for three days this weekend?
description: In March 2024, banks will be closed for 14 days due to Holi 2024, with an extended weekend for multiple states. The closure includes various celebrations like Chapchar Kut and Sivarathri, planned by state governments and the RBI.

title: Key US immigration reform recommendations made by AILA
description: The American Immigration Lawyers Association (AILA) has written to President Joe Biden urging continued immigration reforms. They emphasize the need to address immigrant visa backlogs, expand visa renewal programs, modernize the H-1B visa program, revise shortage occupation lists, and renew regulations for timely work authorization. These recommendations aim to alleviate hardships faced by immigrants and promote economic and social well-being in the United States.

title: NPS security: Two-factor Aadhaar authentication must from Apr 1
description: PFRDA introduces mandatory two-factor Aadhaar authentication for NPS users accessing CRA from April 1, 2024, to enhance security and safeguard stakeholders' interests. The initiative aims to fortify protection against unauthorized access and ensure smooth transition processes.

title: Tanker capsizes off coast of Japan, seven dead
description: The South Korean-flagged chemical tanker, Keoyoung Sun, capsized off Yamaguchi, Japan, resulting in 7 confirmed deaths. 2 crew members have been rescued, with rescue operations ongoing for the remaining individuals.

title: Over 1 million Afghan girls out of school as new school year begins
description: In Afghanistan, Taliban's ban on girls' education affects 1 million students. The ministry excludes female journalists. Agha apologizes. Hanafi aims to expand education. Criticisms from Human Rights Watch persist.

title: I-T cancels long Good Friday weekend from Mar 29-31 for employees
description: The Income Tax Department cancels the long weekend for employees to meet March 31 deadlines. Taxpayers must file TDS, complete assessments, and submit ITR-U to avoid penalties and ensure compliance with tax laws.

title: Gautam Gambhir says 'I can take a bullet for...'
description: Gautam Gambhir's captaincy proved instrumental in propelling Kolkata Knight Riders to the forefront of the IPL, culminating in two title triumphs under his leadership. Now returning to the KKR fold in a mentoring capacity, the former Indian opener brings his wealth of experience to guide and inspire the team. Renowned for his knack for rejuvenating struggling teams, Gambhir's association with KKR dates back to the fourth season of the IPL in 2011.

title: MP man forced to drink urine for eloping with married woman
description: A man in Ujjain district, Madhya Pradesh, faced brutality after eloping with a married woman. He was beaten, forced to drink urine, and wear a garland of shoes by certain individuals. Despite viral videos, the victim has not filed a formal complaint. Police are actively investigating the motive behind this disturbing incident.

title: 'Only time will tell': Harbhajan's take on Rohit-Hardik equation
description: Harbhajan not only hailed Rohit the captain, but the off-spin legend also lauded Sarfaraz Khan, Dhruv Jurel and Yashasvi Jaiswal who were phenomenal in the series. TimesofIndia.com caught up with Harbhajan, who played 103 Tests, 236 ODIs, and 28 T20Is, and spoke about Rohit's leadership, Virat in the T20 World Cup, Yuzvendra Chahal's absence, and much more...

title: First-time ever: US falls out of top 20 in World Happiness Rankings
description: In the latest evaluation, involving more than 140 countries, the US was placed 23rd, a drop from its 15th position the previous year. The report highlighted a significant dip in happiness among Americans under 30, contrasting with the country's top 10 ranking for the happiness of those aged 60 and over. Finland continues its streak as the happiest nation globally for the seventh consecutive year.

title: B'luru blast: Police, EC complaint over Shobha Karandlaje remarks
description: Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin also reacted to the BJP leader's remarks, calling it a 'reckless statement' and said that such assertions could only be made by someone with direct involvement or detailed knowledge of the ongoing investigation into the Rameshwaram cafe blast. He added that Tamilians and Kannadigas alike will reject 'divisive rhetoric of BJP.'

title: 'Some have to be launched multiple times': PM's dig at Rahul
SC agrees to list PIL against freebies
description: Supreme Court to discuss PIL challenging parties' freebies promise. Call for ban on influencing voters with freebies before elections to uphold democratic values and fairness in the electoral process.

title: 'We have a real shot at….': Microsoft CEO Nadella to employees
description: Microsoft introduces Microsoft AI under Mustafa Suleyman's leadership. Satya Nadella highlights innovation. Karén Simonyan joins as Chief Scientist. OpenAI partnership continues. Kevin Scott oversees AI strategy for Microsoft.

title: India has world's third largest startup ecosystem: PM Modi
description: PM Modi lauds India's thriving startup ecosystem at Startup Mahakumbh, highlighting the push for developed nation status, job creators' focus, women-led startups, and equitable technology access, aiming for the world's third-largest economy.

title: Former Telangana governor Tamilisai Soundararajan joins BJP
description: Tamilisai Soundararajan joined the BJP in Chennai on Wednesday, a day after resigning as Telangana governor. Tamil Nadu party leader K Annamalai was also there. Soundararajan's resignation was announced while Prime Minister Modi was holding an election rally in the state's Jagtial district. Tamilisai sent her resignation to President Droupadi Murmu and sent a copy to Modi and Union home minister Amit Shah.

title: How Chinese companies want to ride on Nvidia to bring AI to their cars
description: Leading transportation companies adopt Nvidia Drive Thor for next-gen fleets. Chinese automakers like BYD expand globally with Nvidia. Hyper luxury brand and XPENG also integrate Drive Thor for advanced driving capabilities. Li Auto and ZEEKR follow suit for future vehicle roadmap.

title: TCS may offer 7-8% average salary hikes to these employees
description: TCS plans salary hikes for FY25, with 7-8% for offsite and 2-4% for onsite employees. High performers may receive 12-15% increments. Promotions delayed due to cost concerns, effective April 1, 2024.

title: Virat Kohli asks fans to stop calling him 'King': 'I feel embarrassed'
description: Virat Kohli, the Indian batting maestro, has made a plea to his fans, asking them to avoid addressing him with the title 'King'. Expressing his discomfort with this moniker, Kohli admitted that it caused him embarrassment. Speaking at the lavish unboxing ceremony of RCB's new IPL jersey at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium, where the franchise underwent a rebranding as the Royal Challengers Bengaluru, Virat spoke directly to the crowd.

title: SC to hear Kavitha's plea challenging her arrest on March 22
description: ​Kavitha on Tuesday withdrew her plea from the Supreme Court challenging summons by Enforcement Directorate and filed a fresh writ challenging her arrest. Kavitha in her petition has challenged her remand as well and said the remand order doesn't adhere to Article 141 which states that the law declared by the SC shall be binding on all courts within the territory of India. Kavitha in her plea also challenged section 19 (1) of the PMLA Act.

title: Why Kate's absence continues to fuel media frenzy
description: Kate's absence fuels speculation, stressing visibility for the royal family. Queen Elizabeth II emphasized the need to be seen. Footage near Windsor home combats online conspiracy theories, highlighting monarchal transparency and King Charles III's cancer treatment.

title: Viksit Bharat by 2047 has laser focus on women: Ruchira Kamboj
description: Ruchira Kamboj highlights India's commitment to women-led development, aligning with PM Modi's vision for a fully developed India by 2047. Initiatives like Beti Bachao Beti Padhao and STEM enrollment promote gender equality and women's participation.

title: Rijiju gets addn charge of food processing industries ministry
description: After accepting the resignation of Pashupati Kumar Paras from union council of ministers with immediate effect, President Droupadi Murmu assigned cabinet minister Kiren Rijiju food processing industries ministry, in addition to his existing portfolio of ministry of earth sciences. Paras, Rashtriya Lok Janshakti Party (RLJP) president, submitted his resignation to Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Tuesday.

title: March end of financial year: Coming year for entrepreneurs
description: Financial predictions for zodiac signs advise embracing risk, seeking stability, improving networking, nurturing professional relationships, balancing leadership, fostering creativity, and embracing innovation for a prosperous upcoming year.

title: BMW 620d M Sport Signature launched in India at Rs 78.9 lakh
description: Talking about the powertrain and gearbox, the BMW 620d M Sport signature is powered by a 2.0-litre turbo diesel engine which puts out 190 hp of power and 400 Nm of torque. BMW says the car can sprint from 0-100 kph in 7.9 seconds. The engine comes paired with an 8-speed automatic gearbox.

title: IPL: How DC, LSG, Punjab, RR shape up - a SWOT analysis
description: As Delh Capitals, Lucknow Super Giants and Punjab Kings vie for their first IPL title, it's worth noting that Rajasthan Royals clinched the inaugural title in 2008, led by the legendary Australian leg-spinner, the late Shane Warne. The 2024 season of the cash-rich league begins on March 22 in Chennai.

title: Gadchiroli steel city to be bigger than Jamshedpur: Gadkari
description: Maharashtra govt pushes Gadchiroli as investment hub. Nagpur undergoes infrastructure development with projects like Metro Rail, flyovers. Nagpur envisions becoming logistics capital, focusing on bamboo industry and solid waste treatment for economic growth.

title: Pb govt harassing us over baby's legal status: Moose Wala's dad
description: Sidhu Moose Wala's father accuses govt of harassing over IVF newborn legal status. Legislation impacted older couples. Moose Wala, 29, shot by gangsters Bishnoi and Brar.

title: UP: Amethi villagers threaten poll boycott over missing roads
description: Villagers in Purey Alpi Tiwari hamlet, Sarmeny village, Amethi, display frustrations with infrastructural neglect through a banner saying "no road, no vote", highlighting issues like lack of roads, drainage, and unfulfilled promises leading to a resolve to boycott polls.

title: UP brothers' WagonR to helicopter modification seized by police
description: Brothers in Ambedkar Nagar, UP, garnered attention for transforming a Maruti Suzuki WagonR into a helicopter, but faced police intervention due to unauthorized modifications. The incident showcases the balance between innovation and legal compliance.

title: Watch: Pull, hook, flick! Rohit Sharma sweats it out in nets
description: During the nets session at the Wankhede Stadium ahead of the Indian Premier League (IPL) 2024, Mumbai Indians batsman Rohit Sharma showcased his power-hitting prowess by smashing the ball with force. The five-time champions are set to commence their IPL 2024 journey against the Gujarat Titans on March 24 at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad. MI's official social media account provided a glimpse of Rohit's aggressive batting style during the net sessions.

title: Zomato scraps green uniform for 'pure veg' mode delivery partners
description: In a turn of events, Zomato has announced that it will no longer use green uniforms for its "Pure Veg” fleet delivery partners. The decision comes hours after the company introduced the "Pure Veg Mode" to cater to the dietary preferences of India's significant vegetarian population.

title: Watch: Ravindra Jadeja's iconic moment with MS Dhoni
description: Star all-rounder Ravindra Jadeja, representing India, fondly reminisced about the moment when Chennai Super Kings (CSK) captain MS Dhoni enveloped him in a hug and lifted him. This heartfelt gesture came after Jadeja's exceptional performance led CSK to their record-breaking fifth title, triumphing over the Gujarat Titans in the Indian Premier League (IPL) 2023 final.

title: World's happiest countries: Full list and where India stands
description: Finland continues its streak as the happiest country, with Denmark and Iceland also ranking high. Afghanistan remains at the bottom, while the US drops out of the top 20. Costa Rica and Kuwait see an improvement.

title: Iranian woman Faiza travels to India to wed UP vlogger
description: A UP-based travel vlogger proposed to an Iranian resident, leading to an engagement after she arrived in India, culminating in family support and anticipation for a happy wedding.

title: Watch: How stray dogs at IIT Kanpur reacted to this Robotic dog
description: During IIT Kanpur's Techkriti festival, real dogs interacted with Muks Robotics' AI-powered Robotic dog in a viral Instagram video, showcasing a playful and curious encounter between the animals and the innovative robot.

title: SBI electoral bonds: Infosys and other IT companies in donors list
description: SBI disclosed electoral bond details post-April 2019 as mandated by the Supreme Court, revealing significant donations by IT companies like Infosys, Cyient, and Zensar Technologies, along with notable contributions from Bharti Airtel and Future Gaming.

title: IPL: Challenges ahead for Hardik, Cummins, Gill as new captains
description: The upcoming IPL season is shrouded in intrigue, with leadership changes sparking questions about team dynamics. MI face an awkward transition from Rohit Sharma to Hardik Pandya while Pat Cummins’s demanding workload raises concerns about his ability to lead SRH. Meanwhile, Shubman Gill will take the reins at GT hoping to overcome his lack of experience.

title: Donald Trump, Joe Biden win Ohio primaries of their parties
description: In the latest primary elections, Donald Trump emerged victorious in the Republican primary in Ohio and is poised to win in Arizona, Florida, Illinois, and Kansas. Concurrently, President Joe Biden secured the win in the Ohio Democratic primary and is expected to perform well in the upcoming primaries, except in Florida where the Democratic primary was canceled, awarding all 224 delegates to Biden.
